Western Australia has Great White Sharks it's just a fact. Especially in Salmon season, especially when there are whale carcasses in the water (as there was in the last week). Surfers know the risk. I am vehemently against shark culls and shark nets

The southern part of West Aust, all the way to Victoria, is prime great white territory. I would assume if anyone is a surfer they should know it. The salmon are also running right now, so the sharks are having fun. It annoys me surfers blame sharks for doing what comes naturally
